<paragraph id="537D36A6FFF1FFEFE1FD073AFDCCF8B8" blockId="9.[151,1437,1888,2023]" box="[199,623,1888,1915]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF1FFEFE1FD073AFDCCF8B8" authority="Toth &amp; Varga, 2011" authorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2011" box="[199,623,1888,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosi">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF1FFEFE1FD073AFE25F8B8" bold="true" box="[199,390,1888,1915]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">Melitaea zagrosi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF1FFEFE0B4073BFDCCF8B8" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[398,623,1889,1915]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" pagination="258 - 268" refId="ref11248" refString="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2011) Inter- and intraspecific variation in the genitalia of the ' Melitaea phoebe group' (Lepidoptera. Nymphalidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 258 - 268. [6 pp. of Appendix with key and figures of genitalia only present in the on-line version, www. sciencedirect. com] https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.05.002" type="book chapter" year="2011">Tóth &amp; Varga, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFF1FFECE34D073BFDA8FD46" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFF1FFECE34D073BFDA8FD46" blockId="9.[151,1437,1888,2023]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,933]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">
[TL: 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFF1FFEFE389073BFD40F8B8" box="[691,739,1889,1915]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">Iran</collectingCountry>
, between Kazeroun and Buschir (Konar Takhteh)], subjective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF1FFEFE05507DFFD67F85C" authority="Higgins, 1941" authorityName="Higgins" authorityYear="1941" box="[367,708,1925,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="enoch">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF1FFEFE05507DFFDBEF85C" box="[367,541,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">Melitaea enoch</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF1FFEFE31E07DFFD67F85C" author="Higgins, L. G." box="[548,708,1925,1951]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" pagination="175 - 365" refId="ref9372" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1941) An illustrated catalogue of the Palearctic Melitaea (Lep. Rhopalocera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 91, 175 - 365. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1941. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1941">Higgins, 1941</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF1FFEFE3EE07DFFC9EF85C" bold="true" box="[724,829,1925,1951]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">syn. nov.</emphasis>
). This taxon was distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF1FFEFE5DB07DCFA3FF85C" baseAuthorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1249,1436,1925,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ornata" subSpecies="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF1FFEFE5DB07DCFA3FF85C" box="[1249,1436,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="34">M. ornata abbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of genitalia and wing patterns by 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF1FFEFE39A07F3FC2CF800" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[672,911,1961,1987]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" pagination="258 - 268" refId="ref11248" refString="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2011) Inter- and intraspecific variation in the genitalia of the ' Melitaea phoebe group' (Lepidoptera. Nymphalidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 258 - 268. [6 pp. of Appendix with key and figures of genitalia only present in the on-line version, www. sciencedirect. com] https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.05.002" type="book chapter" year="2011">Tóth &amp; Varga (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF1FFEFE2A107F3FA8AF807" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[923,1321,1961,1988]" pageId="9" pageNumber="34" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 64)</bibRefCitation>
discussed at great length the characters used to distinguish this taxon and considered that they were not sufficiently reliable as diagnostic characters, particularly in view of the fact that the 
<typeStatus id="8C798804FFF2FFECE24F00CDFC0EFF72" box="[885,941,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Type</typeStatus>
Locality of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE50600CDFB2EFF73" authorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2011" box="[1084,1165,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosi">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE50600CDFB2EFF73" box="[1084,1165,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">zagrosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was in the midst of the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE00300E1FE4DFF16" baseAuthorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[313,494,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ornata" subSpecies="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE00300E1FE4DFF16" box="[313,494,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. ornata abbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Zagrosi Mountains (
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE22800E1FBF0FF16" author="Tshikolovets, V. V. &amp; Naderi A. &amp; Eckweiler, W." box="[786,1107,187,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" refId="ref11652" refString="Tshikolovets, V. V., Naderi A. &amp; Eckweiler, W. (2014) The butterflies of Iran and Iraq. Tshikolovets Publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 366 pp. + 65 colour plates." type="book" year="2014">
Tshikolovets 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE29D00E1FC75FF16" box="[935,982,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2014: 320
</bibRefCitation>
, map).Although 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE43400E1FEBEFF3A" author="Tshikolovets, V. V. &amp; Naderi A. &amp; Eckweiler, W." pageId="10" pageNumber="35" refId="ref11652" refString="Tshikolovets, V. V., Naderi A. &amp; Eckweiler, W. (2014) The butterflies of Iran and Iraq. Tshikolovets Publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 366 pp. + 65 colour plates." type="book" year="2014">
Tshikolovets 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE1AD0085FF65FF3A" box="[151,198,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
sank 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE0630085FE6EFF3B" authorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2011" box="[345,461,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosi">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE0630085FE6EFF3B" box="[345,461,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. zagrosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE3A70085FCF0FF3A" baseAuthorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[669,851,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ornata" subSpecies="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE3A70085FCF0FF3A" box="[669,851,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. ornata abbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they acknowledged that there is insufficient material to reach a conclusion regarding the status of the two taxa. The present authors’ only additional comment is that the elevation of the 
<typeStatus id="8C798804FFF2FFECE068017DFE29FE82" box="[338,394,295,321]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Type</typeStatus>
Localities of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE310017DFD4BFE82" baseAuthorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[554,744,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ornata" subSpecies="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE310017DFD4BFE82" box="[554,744,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. ornata abbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="943A9B43FFF2FFECE3C2017CFCF3FE82" box="[760,848,294,321]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="2250.0">2250 m</quantity>
) and the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE53F017DFBF5FE83" authorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2011" box="[1029,1110,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosi">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE53F017DFBF5FE83" box="[1029,1110,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">zagrosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity id="943A9B43FFF2FFECE55D017CFB13FE82" box="[1127,1200,294,321]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="500.0">500 m</quantity>
– Konartakhteh) are very different and environmental differences might account for the differences in wing morphology. 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE4390111FEC1FE4A" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." pageId="10" pageNumber="35" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">Van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014)</bibRefCitation>
have already suggested that small differences in genitalia measurements could be accounted for by the coverslips compressing the genitalia on the slide. Recently 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE28301C9FB24FE6D" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Bereczki, J." box="[953,1159,403,430]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" pagination="106 - 115" refId="ref11405" refString="Toth, J. P., Varga, Z. &amp; Bereczki, J. (2016) Long-term survival and diversification of an endemic Melitaea species in mountains of Iran and adjacent areas. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 54 (2), 106 - 115. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jzs. 12122" type="journal article" year="2016">
Tóth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE2CD01C9FB89FE6E" box="[1015,1066,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, using a combination of morphometric measurements on the genitalia and DNA, elevated the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE2DA01EDFB80FE12" authorityName="Gross &amp; Ebert" authorityYear="1975" box="[992,1059,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE2DA01EDFB80FE12" box="[992,1059,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">abbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to species level and synonymised the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE0390181FEF7FE37" authorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2011" box="[259,340,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosi">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE0390181FEF7FE37" box="[259,340,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">zagrosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with it, in contrast to their previous conclusions, which elevated 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE5190181FBD7FE37" authorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2011" box="[1059,1140,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosi">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE5190181FBD7FE37" box="[1059,1140,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">zagrosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to species level separating it from 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE1D201A5FD2EFDDA" authority="(Toth &amp; Varga 2011)" baseAuthorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[232,653,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ornata" subSpecies="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE1D201A5FE03FDDA" box="[232,416,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. ornata abbas</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE09701A5FD26FDDA" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[429,645,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" pagination="258 - 268" refId="ref11248" refString="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2011) Inter- and intraspecific variation in the genitalia of the ' Melitaea phoebe group' (Lepidoptera. Nymphalidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 258 - 268. [6 pp. of Appendix with key and figures of genitalia only present in the on-line version, www. sciencedirect. com] https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.05.002" type="book chapter" year="2011">Tóth &amp; Varga 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, with further research by 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE29F01A5FBC5FDDA" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Bereczki, J. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Rota, J. &amp; Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N." box="[933,1126,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" pagination="749 - 757" refId="ref11329" refString="Toth, J. P., Bereczki, J., Varga, Z., Rota, J., Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N. (2014) Relationships within the Melitaea phoebe species group (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae): new insights from molecular and morphometric information. Systematic Entomology, 39, 749 - 757. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12083" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tóth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE2E501A5FBACFDDA" box="[991,1039,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
confirming this conclusion. However, their current thinking (
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE32C0279FD7AFDFD" author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Bereczki, J." box="[534,729,547,574]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" pagination="106 - 115" refId="ref11405" refString="Toth, J. P., Varga, Z. &amp; Bereczki, J. (2016) Long-term survival and diversification of an endemic Melitaea species in mountains of Iran and adjacent areas. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 54 (2), 106 - 115. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jzs. 12122" type="journal article" year="2016">
Tóth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE36D0279FD2FFDFE" box="[599,652,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
), appeared to be that 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE2E00279FBE5FDFE" authorityName="Gross &amp; Ebert" authorityYear="1975" box="[986,1094,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE2E00279FBE5FDFE" box="[986,1094,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. abbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE4440279FF4BFDA2" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE4440279FF4BFDA2" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE1CF021DFEC6FDA3" authorityName=", Russell &amp; Tennent" authorityYear="2016" box="[245,357,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE1CF021DFEC6FDA3" box="[245,357,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE0A3021DFDA0FDA2" authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1908" box="[409,515,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telona">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE0A3021DFDA0FDA2" box="[409,515,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. telona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and that the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE3EE021DFC86FDA3" authorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2011" box="[724,805,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosi">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE3EE021DFC86FDA3" box="[724,805,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">zagrosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE2C8021DFBF9FDA2" authorityName="Gross &amp; Ebert" authorityYear="1975" box="[1010,1114,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbas">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE2C8021DFBF9FDA2" box="[1010,1114,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. abbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We place 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE5E8021DFA80FDA3" authorityName="Toth &amp; Varga" authorityYear="2011" box="[1234,1315,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosi">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE5E8021DFA80FDA3" box="[1234,1315,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">zagrosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE0A60231FDA7FD46" authorityName="Higgins" authorityYear="1941" box="[412,516,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="enoch">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE0A60231FDA7FD46" box="[412,516,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. enoch</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
